Planning a trip to Saudi Arabia in 2025? This video provides a clear explanation of the latest travel requirements, including vaccination updates, to help you plan your journey with confidence.

Starting February 15, 2025, new vaccination rules will be strictly enforced for all travelers visiting Saudi Arabia, including those on Umrah, Hajj, or other visas. Here's what you need to know:

Meningococcal Meningitis Vaccine: Mandatory for everyone above 2 years old.
Seasonal Influenza Vaccine: Compulsory for all travelers.
Yellow Fever & Polio Vaccines: Required for visitors from specific reported countries.
Plan your travel accordingly and ensure compliance with these health regulations. Stay informed to make your journey safe and hassle-free!
